FidoNews 1305 & 1306

by Fredrik Bennison
2:205/300, d93fbe@blg.du.se

After reading FidoNews issues 1305 and 1306, I felt sad that
FidoNet had sunk yet another notch down into the treacherous
waters of foul-mouthed flaming in that, I hesitate to call it
article, by C.I.A.

I would like to take this opportunity to thank Mr. Juda on
behalf of all FidoNet sysops, for the service that he has
provided for years, and express a hope that someone or a group
of someones will step in and take the place of fidonet.org.

I'm also saddened by the gloomy future depicted by Mr. Hass,
although I can't say that I agree with it. I still prefer
Fidonet Echomail to Usenet News any day of the week, as it is
much more personal and friendly.

FidoNews 13-08                 Page:  3                    19 Feb 1996

I believe that Fidonet still has a lot to give, at least it does
for me.

